00:08:04.990 --> 00:08:08.510
As imperative it is to
have a system in place,

00:08:08.510 --> 00:08:12.050
it is equally vital to
comprehend the approach

00:08:12.050 --> 00:08:15.430
and response of the building
developers and designers

00:08:15.430 --> 00:08:19.080
towards it to ensure
that we achieve

00:08:19.080 --> 00:08:22.320
our aim of having more
sustainable green buildings

00:08:22.320 --> 00:08:24.570
in the future.

00:08:24.570 --> 00:08:28.100
GBI takes a holistic approach
and covers many aspects

00:08:28.100 --> 00:08:31.400
that facilitate the design and
construction of an environment

00:08:31.400 --> 00:08:35.990
friendly building, grading
them on a 100 point system.

00:08:35.990 --> 00:08:39.140
To assess the impact
of GBI as a system,

00:08:39.140 --> 00:08:42.520
the criterion on which
the buildings are rated

00:08:42.520 --> 00:08:46.700
was sorted into two broad
categories, short term impact,

00:08:46.700 --> 00:08:49.050
and long term impact.

00:08:49.050 --> 00:08:51.970
The categorization depends
on whether the criterion

00:08:51.970 --> 00:08:56.090
helps keeps the building green
for its expected lifetime.

00:08:56.090 --> 00:08:58.820
Long term impact
criterion are mostly

00:08:58.820 --> 00:09:01.220
part of the physical
structure and design

00:09:01.220 --> 00:09:02.910
of the building itself.

00:09:02.910 --> 00:09:07.250
And their energy benefits can
be gained year after year.

00:09:07.250 --> 00:09:11.570
For example, if skylights are
incorporated in the building

00:09:11.570 --> 00:09:13.670
envelope as a passive
design feature

00:09:13.670 --> 00:09:16.170
to optimize the use of daylight.

00:09:16.170 --> 00:09:19.260
Or if advanced energy
performance measures,

00:09:19.260 --> 00:09:21.530
and innovative
design initiatives

00:09:21.530 --> 00:09:25.400
are included at the conception
and construction phase,

00:09:25.400 --> 00:09:27.910
their benefits last
for a lifetime.

00:09:27.910 --> 00:09:31.670
However, other measures,
like worker side amenities,

00:09:31.670 --> 00:09:35.180
or construction waste
management are also important.

00:09:35.180 --> 00:09:38.920
But these are examples of
short term impact criterion,

00:09:38.920 --> 00:09:42.060
as they do not ensure the
effective energy efficiency

00:09:42.060 --> 00:09:46.280
and environmental gain
repeatedly in the coming years.

00:09:46.280 --> 00:09:51.110
GBI has rated around
300 buildings since 2009

00:09:51.110 --> 00:09:52.530
in Malaysia.

00:09:52.530 --> 00:09:56.310
The study was conducted
for the existing GBI

00:09:56.310 --> 00:09:59.830
non-residential new
construction code.

00:09:59.830 --> 00:10:03.490
It was identified that
out of a total 100,

00:10:03.490 --> 00:10:07.720
57 points account for long
term impact criterion,

00:10:07.720 --> 00:10:11.260
and 43 for short term
impact criterion.

00:10:11.260 --> 00:10:14.470
In the past years,
GBI has certified

00:10:14.470 --> 00:10:17.910
112 buildings in
the NRNC category

00:10:17.910 --> 00:10:20.130
under the four classifications.

00:10:20.130 --> 00:10:23.190
Out of these almost
50% of the buildings

00:10:23.190 --> 00:10:26.820
have applied for and
received green certification

00:10:26.820 --> 00:10:32.090
under the rated classification,
which requires only 50 points,

00:10:32.090 --> 00:10:34.850
suggesting that the
majority of buildings

00:10:34.850 --> 00:10:39.790
aim for and receive this
basic level of certification.

00:10:39.790 --> 00:10:42.910
And it may be important to
note that these buildings can

00:10:42.910 --> 00:10:47.520
acquire 84% of their points
from the short term impact

00:10:47.520 --> 00:10:48.810
criterion.

00:10:48.810 --> 00:10:51.640
It is evident from
the data from GBI

00:10:51.640 --> 00:10:55.410
that these building tend to
acquire points from short term

00:10:55.410 --> 00:10:58.390
impact criterion
more, suggesting

00:10:58.390 --> 00:11:01.510
that most of the
buildings rated green

00:11:01.510 --> 00:11:04.920
would not be very different
from the conventional ones

00:11:04.920 --> 00:11:07.010
during their lifespan.

00:11:07.010 --> 00:11:09.380
So the buildings
may be called green,

00:11:09.380 --> 00:11:13.040
but in reality might not
have the expected impact

00:11:13.040 --> 00:11:16.730
on energy use optimization
in Malaysian cities.

00:11:16.730 --> 00:11:19.640
Also identified
were the criterion

00:11:19.640 --> 00:11:22.870
which seemed to be most
achievable and non achievable

00:11:22.870 --> 00:11:24.660
by the buildings.

00:11:24.660 --> 00:11:27.530
Less than 20% of
the rated buildings

00:11:27.530 --> 00:11:31.470
could achieve few of the major
criterion in the long term

00:11:31.470 --> 00:11:33.290
impact category.

00:11:33.290 --> 00:11:35.510
It is interesting
to see that these

00:11:35.510 --> 00:11:40.150
account for almost 25 points
in the 100 point system.

00:11:40.150 --> 00:11:44.650
And the points achieved by more
than 80% of the rated buildings

00:11:44.650 --> 00:11:47.890
have a substantial share of the
short term impact criterion.

00:11:47.890 --> 00:11:52.600
However, from the examples
of platinum, gold, and silver

00:11:52.600 --> 00:11:54.530
rated buildings,
we see that it is

00:11:54.530 --> 00:11:58.430
possible to achieve better
efficiency within the GBI

00:11:58.430 --> 00:11:59.860
framework.

00:11:59.860 --> 00:12:03.220
To encourage and enforce
that on a larger scale

00:12:03.220 --> 00:12:05.920
a few improvisations
can be made.

00:12:05.920 --> 00:12:09.950
Following are suggestions
specific to GBI existing NRNC

00:12:09.950 --> 00:12:10.830
code.

00:12:10.830 --> 00:12:14.540
Malaysian standard MS
1525 is the Malaysian code

00:12:14.540 --> 00:12:17.580
of practice for energy
efficiency and use

00:12:17.580 --> 00:12:21.090
of renewable energy for
non-residential buildings.

00:12:21.090 --> 00:12:25.140
Compliance to it should be
introduced as a prerequisite

00:12:25.140 --> 00:12:27.120
for a GBI rating.

00:12:27.120 --> 00:12:29.980
Among the points
achieved by buildings,

00:12:29.980 --> 00:12:33.190
the percentage requirement
for long term criterion

00:12:33.190 --> 00:12:37.300
should be specified, making
sure that the buildings achieve

00:12:37.300 --> 00:12:38.355
a balance of both.

00:12:38.355 --> 00:12:42.910
A minimum number of long term
criterion points required

00:12:42.910 --> 00:12:46.600
should be fixed to apply for
silver, gold, and platinum

00:12:46.600 --> 00:12:48.520
certification.

00:12:48.520 --> 00:12:50.380
A few of the
identified criterion

00:12:50.380 --> 00:12:53.840
are vital for human health,
comfort, and environment

00:12:53.840 --> 00:12:57.520
protection, therefore
should be made mandatory

00:12:57.520 --> 00:13:00.950
to apply for GBI certification.

00:13:00.950 --> 00:13:03.860
The weightage of
long-term impact criterion

00:13:03.860 --> 00:13:05.680
can be increased.

00:13:05.680 --> 00:13:07.840
This will reinforce
their importance,

00:13:07.840 --> 00:13:12.200
and higher efforts would be put
by developers to achieve them.

00:13:12.200 --> 00:13:16.280
The number of points allotted
for innovation criterion

00:13:16.280 --> 00:13:17.950
should be increased.

00:13:17.950 --> 00:13:21.240
This encourage designers
to be creative and make

00:13:21.240 --> 00:13:24.460
proper analysis of the
behavior of the designs

00:13:24.460 --> 00:13:26.590
and specifications.

00:13:26.590 --> 00:13:29.200
Innovation should be
encouraged in design,

00:13:29.200 --> 00:13:32.010
rather than just being
limited to technology,

00:13:32.010 --> 00:13:35.390
by equally dividing innovation
points among building design

00:13:35.390 --> 00:13:39.490
features and technology
incorporation.

00:13:39.490 --> 00:13:42.360
Learning the lessons from
the examples of environment

00:13:42.360 --> 00:13:45.760
sensitive buildings in Malaysia,
and looking at their climate

00:13:45.760 --> 00:13:49.070
responsive architectural
design and solutions

00:13:49.070 --> 00:13:52.840
can be one of the most
effective ways of doing this.

00:13:52.840 --> 00:13:57.050
These buildings have been built
for the Malaysian climate,

00:13:57.050 --> 00:14:01.660
with features like solar buffer
effect, solar shading devices,

00:14:01.660 --> 00:14:04.919
day lighting, terraced
gardens, and orientation

00:14:04.919 --> 00:14:05.710
driven ventilation.

00:14:05.710 --> 00:14:09.540
These are a few of the
celebrated environment

00:14:09.540 --> 00:14:12.820
sensitive buildings in Malaysia.

00:14:12.820 --> 00:14:16.100
Encouraging architects
to apply these features

00:14:16.100 --> 00:14:18.730
under innovative
design criterion, which

00:14:18.730 --> 00:14:21.770
promote the use of climate
responsive architecture,

00:14:21.770 --> 00:14:25.990
these suggestions may help bring
about substantial benefits,

00:14:25.990 --> 00:14:30.330
